WEBVTT

1
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:31.031
Emerson. are you with the patient?

2
00:00:32.658 --> 00:00:34.576
Stationed outside her room. ma'am.

3
00:00:34.660 --> 00:00:37.538
Good. I need you to deliver
a message to her nurse.

4
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:43.043
What are you doing here?

5
00:00:43.669 --> 00:00:45.712
Figured you might need some company.

6
00:00:48.799 --> 00:00:52.803
What I really need is for you
to start the Judicial process

7
00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:54.429
for installing an interim mayor.

8
00:00:54.513 --> 00:00:55.722
Her condition's that bad?

9
00:00:55.806 --> 00:00:58.934
Unlikely to survive the night.
I'll see you at home.

10
00:00:59.017 --> 00:01:00.936
It wants what it wanted three months ago.

11
00:01:01.019 --> 00:01:04.565
but the gas in the mines
didn't quite do the job. right?

12
00:01:05.566 --> 00:01:07.693
The gas in the mines was for Lukas Kyle.

13
00:01:07.776 --> 00:01:09.278
He was in the mines?

14
00:01:09.361 --> 00:01:10.571
He got away.

15
00:01:11.655 --> 00:01:13.490
But the gas did get the mayor.

16
00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:20.581
Well. it sounds like the voice in there
thinks that was a good thing.

17
00:01:22.124 --> 00:01:23.625
Heroic death and all.

18
00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:26.587
And this.

19
00:01:27.880 --> 00:01:30.716
this could stop the need
to put the drugs in the water.

20
00:01:34.469 --> 00:01:35.846
I'll do it for you.

21
00:01:38.682 --> 00:01:40.100
It has to be me.

22
00:01:40.184 --> 00:01:42.603
Yeah. I understand.

23
00:01:43.896 --> 00:01:45.772
But you don't have to be alone.

24
00:01:51.486 --> 00:01:53.363
When will Mrs. Sims get here?

25
00:01:53.447 --> 00:01:54.823
She's on her way now.

26
00:01:56.617 --> 00:01:58.619
She wants her unconscious
when she arrives.

27
00:02:03.874 --> 00:02:05.083
Hold her down.

28
00:02:11.715 --> 00:02:13.091
What's going on?

29
00:02:13.175 --> 00:02:15.719
- Okay. Okay.
- No.

30
00:02:15.802 --> 00:02:18.680
Hey. Hey. hey. hey.

31
00:02:18.764 --> 00:02:20.766
- It's okay. It's all right.
- Help! Help!

32
00:02:20.849 --> 00:02:24.269
- Keep her quiet.
- Help! Help!

33
00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:43.330
No. no. no. no.

34
00:03:12.985 --> 00:03:15.696
We have to go. Now.

35
00:05:14.106 --> 00:05:16.984
- Hey. Hey. hey. What are you doing?
- We have to call someone.

36
00:05:17.067 --> 00:05:18.527
We have to call someone?

37
00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:20.153
What the fuck?

38
00:05:20.237 --> 00:05:22.364
- They just made a man disappear. okay?
- Goddamn it!

39
00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:24.575
And they're probably listening
through our phones.

40
00:05:24.658 --> 00:05:26.869
- What if Charlotte tries to call?
- You can't...

41
00:05:27.369 --> 00:05:29.997
Daniel. you can't talk to Charlotte.
They'll be monitoring her calls.

42
00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:31.832
We have to get away from here.
I just don't know...

43
00:05:31.915 --> 00:05:33.750
- Wait. What...
- ...if my car is bugged or has a tracker.

44
00:05:33.834 --> 00:05:35.377
What do you think this is?

45
00:05:38.255 --> 00:05:41.508
Someone made that man disappear.

46
00:05:43.468 --> 00:05:44.469
Okay?

47
00:05:45.554 --> 00:05:47.556
So now we have to get somewhere safe.

48
00:05:50.976 --> 00:05:52.519
I think I know somewhere.

49
00:05:52.603 --> 00:05:53.604
Where?

50
00:05:56.607 --> 00:06:00.068
Okay. just don't show up until 10:00.

51
00:06:01.195 --> 00:06:02.779
What am I supposed to do until then?

52
00:06:03.572 --> 00:06:05.449
Whatever you do. don't go home.

53
00:06:10.204 --> 00:06:11.622
You'll be all right. Nurse!

54
00:06:17.377 --> 00:06:19.129
- Tell me she's okay.
- I don't know.

55
00:06:19.213 --> 00:06:20.756
I tried to stay with her.
They wouldn't let me.

56
00:06:20.839 --> 00:06:22.841
- I'm a total piece of shit.
- What are you talking about?

57
00:06:22.925 --> 00:06:24.593
Jules reached out to me for help.

58
00:06:24.676 --> 00:06:27.304
First I ignored her
and then I yelled at her.

59
00:06:27.387 --> 00:06:30.140
You can't beat yourself up.
I left her alone in the mines.

60
00:06:30.224 --> 00:06:32.434
- What happened to her?
- She went in to try and save people.

61
00:06:32.518 --> 00:06:33.852
Of course she did.

62
00:06:33.936 --> 00:06:35.604
They're not gonna let you see her.

63
00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:53.539
Hey. Emerson.

64
00:06:53.622 --> 00:06:55.040
She's got a pulse.

65
00:06:56.250 --> 00:06:57.251
Fuck.

66
00:07:02.631 --> 00:07:06.760
Okay. Here. Take this. Breathe. Breathe.
Breathe. Okay. Good.

67
00:07:11.807 --> 00:07:13.141
We gotta go. We gotta go.

68
00:07:19.898 --> 00:07:21.024
Sheriff.

69
00:07:34.329 --> 00:07:36.290
So. what do you wanna know?

70
00:07:36.373 --> 00:07:38.625
Just wanna confirm cause of death
was rat poison.

71
00:07:38.709 --> 00:07:41.170
- Can't do that.
- You need more time?

72
00:07:41.253 --> 00:07:42.838
No. I mean. she wasn't poisoned.

73
00:07:43.964 --> 00:07:47.843
I got a full house tonight whose C.O.D.
was aerosol-based rat poison.

74
00:07:47.926 --> 00:07:49.511
Their lungs are fried.

75
00:07:49.595 --> 00:07:51.680
Hers are kitchen clean.

76
00:07:51.763 --> 00:07:53.015
Then what happened?

77
00:07:53.098 --> 00:07:55.392
She was struck
in the back of the head. hard.

78
00:07:55.976 --> 00:07:58.645
Pretty sure by a length of rebar.

79
00:07:58.729 --> 00:08:00.731
There's a ribbed pattern in the wound.

80
00:08:00.814 --> 00:08:03.942
- When?
- By the pooling? Couple days.

81
00:08:07.863 --> 00:08:09.114
Where did you find her?

82
00:08:09.198 --> 00:08:12.701
One of the search teams went down
a closed-off tunnel. just to be sure.

83
00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:14.620
Found her way back.

84
00:08:14.703 --> 00:08:18.749
Maybe she was there for some reason.
and a ceiling caved in?

85
00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:21.793
- They use rebar--
- No. When I said her lungs were clean.

86
00:08:21.877 --> 00:08:23.670
I meant she didn't die in the mines.

87
00:08:24.379 --> 00:08:27.299
Anyone who dies in there.
and I've seen a bunch over the years.

88
00:08:27.382 --> 00:08:29.593
there's always dust in the lungs.

89
00:08:32.596 --> 00:08:34.597
She was never supposed to be found.

90
00:08:39.770 --> 00:08:41.730
Show me the wound. please.

91
00:08:42.940 --> 00:08:44.608
Billings to Deputy Murphy.

92
00:08:45.484 --> 00:08:46.527
<i>Go ahead. Sheriff.</i>

93
00:08:47.236 --> 00:08:49.780
If you see Carla McLain.
tell her to meet me in Supply.

94
00:08:50.364 --> 00:08:51.865
It's about her shadow.

95
00:08:51.949 --> 00:08:53.242
<i>You find her?</i>

96
00:08:55.035 --> 00:08:56.036
Yeah.

97
00:09:02.209 --> 00:09:04.962
Okay. Not what I was expecting.

98
00:09:06.380 --> 00:09:08.173
Obviously not your place.

99
00:09:09.842 --> 00:09:11.260
What's that supposed to mean?

100
00:09:12.094 --> 00:09:16.932
Just that you drive a 30-year-old Saab.
Not ironically.

101
00:09:17.015 --> 00:09:18.016
And...

102
00:09:19.643 --> 00:09:21.854
this is different.

103
00:09:22.729 --> 00:09:26.817
For the record.
I helped pick out the furniture.

104
00:09:31.655 --> 00:09:32.698
For who?

105
00:09:35.242 --> 00:09:38.036
Palmer. My ex.

106
00:09:39.288 --> 00:09:44.042
And this Palmer is okay with you
just coming in and out whenever you want?

107
00:09:44.126 --> 00:09:45.961
He's on assignment in South Sudan.

108
00:09:47.254 --> 00:09:48.380
All right.

109
00:09:49.840 --> 00:09:51.216
- Hey.
- Yeah.

110
00:09:52.843 --> 00:09:54.052
Take off your shoes.

111
00:10:07.816 --> 00:10:09.359
Wow.

112
00:10:09.443 --> 00:10:13.572
First thing I do when a relationship ends
is bury all evidence deep in the earth.

113
00:10:13.655 --> 00:10:17.659
But this guy's got a giant photo of you
up on his wall.

114
00:10:19.077 --> 00:10:21.246
Yeah. Palmer is not like that.

115
00:10:21.330 --> 00:10:22.497
Like what?

116
00:10:22.581 --> 00:10:23.749
Petty.

117
00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:26.335
So that's what you're into?

118
00:10:26.418 --> 00:10:30.339
- Not-petty. Pulitzer-winning type guys.
- God. it was not a date.

119
00:10:34.218 --> 00:10:35.552
There any food?

120
00:10:35.636 --> 00:10:36.637
Help yourself.

121
00:10:37.429 --> 00:10:39.598
Where'd you go between Steve's and here?

122
00:10:39.681 --> 00:10:41.975
Just walked around.
tried to clear my head. You?

123
00:10:42.059 --> 00:10:43.310
The office.

124
00:10:43.393 --> 00:10:45.354
What office? You were fired.

125
00:10:45.437 --> 00:10:47.564
Kept my key card. Needed a computer.

126
00:10:48.357 --> 00:10:52.444
Okay. So. I did a bunch of searches
on Steve's address.

127
00:10:52.528 --> 00:10:54.947
Turns out. actually his name.
Steven Price.

128
00:10:55.030 --> 00:10:57.658
Finally got what I thought
was going to be his cell.

129
00:10:57.741 --> 00:11:00.244
Recording said the number was not in use.

130
00:11:00.327 --> 00:11:01.328
Maybe it wasn't his.

131
00:11:01.411 --> 00:11:04.456
Well. then I called the number for
the father of Charlotte's squadron leader.

132
00:11:04.540 --> 00:11:05.582
- Mr. Alameda.
- Yep.

133
00:11:05.666 --> 00:11:07.751
Recording said the number was not in use.

134
00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:11.255
It was working the day before yesterday.

135
00:11:13.423 --> 00:11:15.342
Who the fuck are we dealing with?

136
00:11:19.721 --> 00:11:21.098
So do we go to the police?

137
00:11:22.349 --> 00:11:25.686
I'm guessing they're the kind of people
who would make sure that goes nowhere.

138
00:11:27.396 --> 00:11:29.147
These expired two years ago.

139
00:11:32.025 --> 00:11:33.318
No. stop.

140
00:11:34.194 --> 00:11:35.195
Here.

141
00:11:37.155 --> 00:11:39.491
- You had these the whole time?
- What is our next move?

142
00:11:41.201 --> 00:11:42.452
Do we even have one?

143
00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:45.622
I mean. without that comms recording.
we are move-less.

144
00:11:46.248 --> 00:11:50.335
Well. he said someone in Moldova
recorded the unencrypted comms.

145
00:11:52.421 --> 00:11:54.882
If we could find out who that is.

146
00:11:55.382 --> 00:11:58.760
maybe we can get another copy
of the recording. Leak it.

147
00:12:00.721 --> 00:12:02.931
How do we find someone
we know nothing about?

148
00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:13.901
You know. at Steve's. that chess game.

149
00:12:13.984 --> 00:12:17.613
Weird. right? It's like his whole mood
shifted when his turn was up.

150
00:12:17.696 --> 00:12:19.031
There was something going on.

151
00:12:19.114 --> 00:12:23.493
He was. like. a couple of moves away
from mate. and he just exposed his king.

152
00:12:24.161 --> 00:12:25.829
Maybe he was just distracted.

153
00:12:25.913 --> 00:12:27.623
And what if he wasn't playing to win?

154
00:12:29.082 --> 00:12:30.959
What if he was playing to communicate?

155
00:12:31.043 --> 00:12:32.044
What do you mean?

156
00:12:34.338 --> 00:12:35.339
Okay.

157
00:12:35.923 --> 00:12:39.051
When Snowden leaked
those NSA documents in 2013.

158
00:12:39.551 --> 00:12:42.554
it came out that government agents were
using <i>World of Warcraft</i>

159
00:12:42.638 --> 00:12:44.723
to infiltrate terrorist organizations.

160
00:12:44.806 --> 00:12:49.311
They thought the terrorists might be
using online games to communicate.

161
00:12:50.312 --> 00:12:51.688
What would he be trying to say?

162
00:12:52.606 --> 00:12:57.402
I don't know.
The king... the king has fallen?

163
00:12:58.111 --> 00:12:59.613
Look. it doesn't matter what he meant.

164
00:12:59.696 --> 00:13:01.490
If we can just find out
who his opponent was.

165
00:13:02.115 --> 00:13:03.534
we may have another lead.

166
00:13:04.159 --> 00:13:05.619
How do we do that?

167
00:13:06.828 --> 00:13:11.583
Okay. I caught just the tail end
of his username.

168
00:13:13.544 --> 00:13:18.006
It was something. something...

169
00:13:20.843 --> 00:13:22.261
"big foot lives."

170
00:13:26.223 --> 00:13:27.558
Well. that's ridiculous.

171
00:13:29.059 --> 00:13:31.061
- Great. We got him.
- A little.

172
00:13:31.144 --> 00:13:32.396
It's what I saw.

173
00:13:35.023 --> 00:13:36.149
What?

174
00:13:36.233 --> 00:13:38.443
Well. you're good at this. Nancy Drew.

175
00:13:40.404 --> 00:13:42.322
No. no. Don't call me that.

176
00:13:42.406 --> 00:13:45.117
They called you that at school?
It's a sore point?

177
00:13:45.200 --> 00:13:46.952
Call me that again. Find out.

178
00:13:48.036 --> 00:13:50.455
I'll kill you.
I'll kill you in your sleep.

179
00:14:20.068 --> 00:14:23.030
Lukas fucking Kyle.

180
00:14:23.113 --> 00:14:24.948
They tell me you've been looking for me.

181
00:14:26.200 --> 00:14:29.953
Okay. I'm afraid you're not gonna like
what I have to say.

182
00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:33.123
What do you have to say?

183
00:14:34.249 --> 00:14:37.377
You and your Outsiders keep
telling people it's safe outside.

184
00:14:38.462 --> 00:14:41.423
- Because it is.
- No. It isn't.

185
00:14:42.508 --> 00:14:45.010
What you see on the screens
in the cafeteria.

186
00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:47.554
that's exactly what it's like.

187
00:14:55.646 --> 00:14:58.357
Fuck me.

188
00:15:01.527 --> 00:15:03.820
They got to you.
No wonder we couldn't find him.

189
00:15:03.904 --> 00:15:06.323
He was probably their guest
in a big apartment up top.

190
00:15:06.406 --> 00:15:07.533
I've been in the mines.

191
00:15:07.616 --> 00:15:10.911
I've seen the cleaning video. asshole.

192
00:15:10.994 --> 00:15:12.746
I know that they're lying.

193
00:15:13.330 --> 00:15:16.333
It is a fucking paradise out there.

194
00:15:17.167 --> 00:15:19.169
That video gets put in the helmets

195
00:15:19.253 --> 00:15:23.215
so whoever they send outside
actually cleans.

196
00:15:29.471 --> 00:15:30.806
Video in the helmet?

197
00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:44.570
You believe him?

198
00:15:44.653 --> 00:15:45.654
Why would he lie?

199
00:15:46.238 --> 00:15:47.573
"Why would he lie?"

200
00:15:47.656 --> 00:15:48.991
- Are you fucking--
- Shit.

201
00:15:49.616 --> 00:15:50.826
What are you doing?

202
00:15:51.743 --> 00:15:53.912
Raiders are looking for somebody.
This level's crawling.

203
00:15:53.996 --> 00:15:54.997
All right.

204
00:15:55.080 --> 00:15:58.166
Look. whether you believe me
or not. it doesn't matter.

205
00:15:58.250 --> 00:16:00.294
These three kept me from being hauled in
by the raiders.

206
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:02.671
And they wanted me to meet you.
I figured I owed them that.

207
00:16:02.754 --> 00:16:03.755
- but now I gotta go.
- No!

208
00:16:03.839 --> 00:16:05.507
Great. Go back to your big pals up top.

209
00:16:05.591 --> 00:16:08.051
Hey. Juliette came looking for me
in the mines.

210
00:16:08.135 --> 00:16:09.303
I'm gonna find her.

211
00:16:09.386 --> 00:16:12.014
- Move.
- Nobody's going anywhere. Stay. Stop it.

212
00:16:12.973 --> 00:16:13.974
Shit.

213
00:16:14.057 --> 00:16:16.143
Judicial Security. Open up.

214
00:16:17.102 --> 00:16:18.687
Judicial Security. Open up.

215
00:16:19.897 --> 00:16:21.398
Judicial Security. Open up.

216
00:16:24.776 --> 00:16:26.403
Looks like you're stuck with us.

217
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:32.117
- Step back.
- My friend's in there

218
00:16:32.201 --> 00:16:33.911
fighting for her life. I need to see her.

219
00:16:33.994 --> 00:16:36.455
This area is on lockdown.
Nobody in or out.

220
00:16:36.538 --> 00:16:38.081
If you don't step back--

221
00:16:38.165 --> 00:16:40.125
- What are you gonna do?
- Hey. hey. Shirl.

222
00:16:44.087 --> 00:16:45.255
We tried. Shirl.

223
00:16:47.466 --> 00:16:50.219
What if she doesn't make it?
What if we don't get to see her?

224
00:16:50.302 --> 00:16:53.597
You're definitely not gonna see her if
you're locked up for assaulting a raider.

225
00:16:55.224 --> 00:16:56.558
Let me talk to him.

226
00:17:03.232 --> 00:17:04.733
I didn't introduce myself.

227
00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:06.401
My name is Knox.

228
00:17:07.069 --> 00:17:08.529
I'm the head of Mechanical.

229
00:17:08.612 --> 00:17:12.031
My friend here. she and the mayor have
known each other since they were kids.

230
00:17:12.574 --> 00:17:16.203
She just wants to say hey. tell her she's
thinking of her. then she'll be right out.

231
00:17:17.454 --> 00:17:18.789
Head of Mechanical. huh?

232
00:17:20.082 --> 00:17:21.541
You led the rebellion.

233
00:17:22.917 --> 00:17:24.586
- Well--
- I was down there in the generator room.

234
00:17:24.670 --> 00:17:26.296
Saw all that gunpowder.

235
00:17:26.839 --> 00:17:29.716
I said. instead of marching you upstairs.
we should put you all in there

236
00:17:29.800 --> 00:17:31.093
with the gunpowder.

237
00:17:32.177 --> 00:17:33.512
then light a match.

238
00:17:34.680 --> 00:17:35.931
What do you think?

239
00:17:42.020 --> 00:17:43.021
I think...

240
00:17:44.481 --> 00:17:46.066
I think you're entitled to your opinion.

241
00:17:49.236 --> 00:17:50.779
This is mine.

242
00:17:57.536 --> 00:17:58.579
Fuck!

243
00:18:23.061 --> 00:18:26.356
We have a situation.
Mayor Nichols is somewhere on this level.

244
00:18:26.440 --> 00:18:28.108
She may be with the nurse.

245
00:18:28.775 --> 00:18:31.153
All the cameras in Medical were shut down.

246
00:18:31.987 --> 00:18:35.073
You take this corridor.
You take that corridor.

247
00:18:35.157 --> 00:18:37.618
But remember. I need you to be discreet.

248
00:18:54.676 --> 00:18:56.512
How did we miss this. Rob? How?

249
00:18:56.595 --> 00:18:58.263
We handpicked that nurse.

250
00:18:58.347 --> 00:18:59.473
You said she was loyal.

251
00:18:59.556 --> 00:19:02.559
- Always followed orders.
- She did. until now.

252
00:19:02.643 --> 00:19:03.644
Until...

253
00:19:03.727 --> 00:19:05.854
She must've sensed
why you were coming down.

254
00:19:05.938 --> 00:19:07.356
If we don't get this done...

255
00:19:07.439 --> 00:19:09.191
- We will.
- How?

256
00:19:09.942 --> 00:19:12.236
I know the nurse's file pretty well.

257
00:19:12.319 --> 00:19:16.156
If they get off this level. I have an idea
where she might take Nichols.

258
00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:18.825
- Where?
- She has family down below.

259
00:19:18.909 --> 00:19:20.619
Okay. Send raiders.

260
00:19:20.702 --> 00:19:23.747
Camille. we need to handle this quietly.

261
00:19:26.333 --> 00:19:27.584
I'll get ahead of them.

262
00:19:28.585 --> 00:19:30.504
This has to end tonight. Rob.

263
00:19:31.088 --> 00:19:33.882
I'll take care of her myself.

264
00:19:47.604 --> 00:19:49.857
Johnny. if you find them.
keep it off the radio.

265
00:19:49.940 --> 00:19:51.275
Send a message straight to my office.

266
00:19:51.358 --> 00:19:54.653
We have people on this level.
Send someone to levels above and below.

267
00:19:54.736 --> 00:19:57.906
And when Emerson comes to.
I want anything useful she can remember.

268
00:19:57.990 --> 00:20:00.617
She's alive and she's gotten away.

269
00:20:00.701 --> 00:20:03.537
- Oh. shit.
- I think Sims and his wife want her dead.

270
00:20:03.620 --> 00:20:05.414
What? Why?

271
00:20:05.497 --> 00:20:06.748
No idea.

272
00:20:10.335 --> 00:20:11.587
I need to follow him.

273
00:20:12.087 --> 00:20:14.506
Hey. you! Stop talking to him.

274
00:20:14.590 --> 00:20:16.508
Step away from the prisoner.
or you're gonna join him.

275
00:20:16.592 --> 00:20:19.261
Just telling him this is what he gets
for being an asshole.

276
00:20:28.478 --> 00:20:30.230
This room is locked. You have the key?

277
00:20:30.314 --> 00:20:32.441
They're going to see us
as soon as we leave.

278
00:20:32.524 --> 00:20:34.443
We're not leaving through the door.

279
00:20:34.526 --> 00:20:37.654
I basically grew up in Medical.
and I found out a long time ago.

280
00:20:37.738 --> 00:20:41.700
someone got tired of going all the way to
the stairs to get down to the next level.

281
00:20:45.245 --> 00:20:46.788
Okay. come on. Let's go. Let's go.

282
00:20:46.872 --> 00:20:48.415
Hey. No.

283
00:20:48.498 --> 00:20:50.709
Listen. I'm the reason
you started getting your memory back.

284
00:20:50.792 --> 00:20:53.837
- I took you off the forgetting drugs.
- No. I spit them out.

285
00:20:53.921 --> 00:20:56.298
Okay. even before that.
someone asked me to replace them.

286
00:20:56.381 --> 00:20:58.175
- Who?
- Look. we don't have time for that.

287
00:20:58.258 --> 00:21:00.969
Right now.
your choice is with me or the raiders.

288
00:21:20.072 --> 00:21:21.073
Hello?

289
00:21:30.374 --> 00:21:32.167
Oh. sorry.
I thought I was the only one here.

290
00:21:32.251 --> 00:21:34.211
She's friendly. Don't worry.

291
00:21:34.294 --> 00:21:35.671
Sheriff Billings.

292
00:21:36.880 --> 00:21:38.298
I've never met one of you before.

293
00:21:38.799 --> 00:21:41.176
You know.
we don't get a lot of sheriffs visiting.

294
00:21:41.260 --> 00:21:42.761
especially in the middle of the night.

295
00:21:44.096 --> 00:21:46.098
I'm looking for Carla McLain.

296
00:21:46.890 --> 00:21:50.018
McLain? She hasn't
been up here for months.

297
00:21:50.102 --> 00:21:51.103
I'm expecting her.

298
00:21:51.186 --> 00:21:52.229
Fair enough.

299
00:21:52.312 --> 00:21:53.897
- Nice to meet you. Sheriff.
- Yeah.

300
00:21:56.316 --> 00:21:57.860
- What's your name?
- Mike.

301
00:21:58.485 --> 00:22:00.237
- Mike what?
- Davidson.

302
00:22:01.321 --> 00:22:04.408
Orla Kent's boyfriend.
Got your name from her sister.

303
00:22:04.491 --> 00:22:06.243
Oh. right. Yeah. of course.

304
00:22:07.244 --> 00:22:08.829
Sheila. Yeah.

305
00:22:10.122 --> 00:22:12.082
Have you found Orla yet?

306
00:22:12.165 --> 00:22:13.542
Hope to soon.

307
00:22:15.002 --> 00:22:18.005
- When was the last time you saw her?
- Here. at work.

308
00:22:18.088 --> 00:22:19.298
Just outside Critical Supply.

309
00:22:19.381 --> 00:22:20.507
How'd she seem?

310
00:22:21.049 --> 00:22:22.593
- In what way?
- Her mood.

311
00:22:22.676 --> 00:22:24.553
- What she talked about...
- Oh. yeah. No. no.

312
00:22:24.636 --> 00:22:26.471
She seemed good. Yeah.

313
00:22:26.555 --> 00:22:29.141
She'd just been up at that... council thing.

314
00:22:29.641 --> 00:22:31.059
And she was on her way home.

315
00:22:31.143 --> 00:22:32.394
- You go with her?
- No. no.

316
00:22:32.477 --> 00:22:35.272
I was too focused on giving Dandy here
some exercise.

317
00:22:35.355 --> 00:22:36.815
Yeah. the bay we were in was deep.

318
00:22:36.899 --> 00:22:39.193
It means I can throw the ball
and give her a good run.

319
00:22:40.319 --> 00:22:43.405
Yeah. we said goodbye
and I haven't seen her since.

320
00:22:43.488 --> 00:22:45.199
But you don't seem too worried.

321
00:22:48.243 --> 00:22:51.663
Orla's more independent
than people think. family included.

322
00:22:52.497 --> 00:22:54.708
You know. I'm sure there's...

323
00:22:54.791 --> 00:22:57.419
plenty of things she's gotten into that
even I don't know about.

324
00:23:02.090 --> 00:23:04.510
- Thank you for your time.
- See you.

325
00:23:14.853 --> 00:23:16.480
They've moved on from Medical.

326
00:23:20.067 --> 00:23:21.944
Here. take this. Take it.

327
00:23:25.447 --> 00:23:28.408
By Judicial order.
open the door immediately!

328
00:23:33.872 --> 00:23:35.207
Open up!

329
00:23:37.084 --> 00:23:39.419
All right. Okay. deep breaths. Okay?

330
00:23:40.087 --> 00:23:42.840
Listen. I'll draw them away from you.

331
00:23:43.715 --> 00:23:45.217
When it's safe. go to the...

332
00:23:45.801 --> 00:23:47.928
When it's safe. go to the pump room on 76.

333
00:23:48.011 --> 00:23:50.472
- What? Okay.
- Okay? Seventy-six. Good.

334
00:23:50.556 --> 00:23:52.391
Wait. wait. wait. Wait. Hey!

335
00:23:57.145 --> 00:23:59.022
That's the nurse. Grab her.

336
00:23:59.106 --> 00:24:00.107
Hey!

337
00:24:00.190 --> 00:24:02.734
No. no! Let me go!

338
00:24:02.818 --> 00:24:03.819
Where's the mayor?

339
00:24:03.902 --> 00:24:06.405
- She's passed out in Medical.
- Show us.

340
00:24:37.644 --> 00:24:38.645
Daniel?

341
00:24:47.154 --> 00:24:48.488
He ran.

342
00:24:49.615 --> 00:24:50.824
He fucking ran.

343
00:24:57.331 --> 00:24:58.332
Hey.

344
00:24:58.916 --> 00:25:00.709
- Hey.
- What?

345
00:25:01.919 --> 00:25:03.337
I thought you chickened out.

346
00:25:04.254 --> 00:25:05.255
So you missed me?

347
00:25:07.674 --> 00:25:08.884
Where'd you even go?

348
00:25:09.885 --> 00:25:10.886
Oh. my God.

349
00:25:10.969 --> 00:25:14.097
There are black ops assholes after us.

350
00:25:14.181 --> 00:25:15.891
and you think doughnuts?

351
00:25:15.974 --> 00:25:17.726
And bear claws.

352
00:25:19.102 --> 00:25:20.103
You're an idiot.

353
00:25:20.938 --> 00:25:22.481
There's a bodega around the corner.

354
00:25:22.564 --> 00:25:26.026
The owner wouldn't let me use his phone
unless I spent ten bucks. so breakfast.

355
00:25:26.109 --> 00:25:27.736
No. I told you we couldn't call Charlotte.

356
00:25:27.819 --> 00:25:29.112
I didn't call Charlotte.

357
00:25:29.196 --> 00:25:31.865
But get dressed.
we have an appointment in an hour.

358
00:25:31.949 --> 00:25:33.200
What? Where?

359
00:25:35.410 --> 00:25:36.411
The Pentagon.

360
00:26:12.990 --> 00:26:14.950
You need to listen to me.

361
00:26:18.245 --> 00:26:19.454
Move.

362
00:26:20.163 --> 00:26:21.164
Go.

363
00:26:23.667 --> 00:26:24.960
Go. go. go.

364
00:26:26.587 --> 00:26:27.588
Hey!

365
00:26:28.589 --> 00:26:32.092
- They are trying to kill you.
- Okay.

366
00:26:33.218 --> 00:26:35.345
How the fuck did he know
that I was gonna go there?

367
00:26:35.429 --> 00:26:37.681
We gotta get down to Mechanical.
We got places we can hide you.

368
00:26:37.764 --> 00:26:39.850
I need... I need to find Lukas.

369
00:26:39.933 --> 00:26:41.393
Lukas is dead.

370
00:26:41.894 --> 00:26:42.895
No. I...

371
00:26:44.188 --> 00:26:47.399
No. I talked to him.
I saw him in the mines. No.

372
00:26:49.610 --> 00:26:51.820
Okay. can you at least take me
where you took him?

373
00:26:51.904 --> 00:26:53.447
The Digger Void is sealed off.

374
00:26:54.907 --> 00:26:56.950
Okay. can you take me as far as you can?

375
00:26:59.620 --> 00:27:00.829
Fine.

376
00:27:08.629 --> 00:27:10.881
Kenny G in the flesh.

377
00:27:10.964 --> 00:27:13.634
God. Sam the Ram.

378
00:27:15.344 --> 00:27:16.345
You look good. man.

379
00:27:16.428 --> 00:27:17.679
That's my assistant Helen.

380
00:27:17.763 --> 00:27:19.181
- Hi. nice to meet you.
- Sam Ramsey.

381
00:27:19.264 --> 00:27:21.266
- Shall we go for a walk? Yeah.
- Yeah. Let's go.

382
00:27:21.350 --> 00:27:22.434
How do you two know each other?

383
00:27:22.518 --> 00:27:24.686
- We served overseas.
- Yeah. no big deal.

384
00:27:24.770 --> 00:27:26.980
We were in a band.

385
00:27:27.064 --> 00:27:29.316
- You were in a band?
- The Lost Boys.

386
00:27:30.317 --> 00:27:31.652
- Uh-huh.
- No. no. no. no.

387
00:27:31.735 --> 00:27:33.529
- Yeah. we did '80s covers.
- No.

388
00:27:33.612 --> 00:27:34.696
Your old boss here used to

389
00:27:34.780 --> 00:27:36.156
- shred on the sax...
- Wow.

390
00:27:36.240 --> 00:27:38.242
...back before we became
boring civil servants.

391
00:27:38.325 --> 00:27:39.868
At least you get to hang out
at the Pentagon.

392
00:27:39.952 --> 00:27:41.662
I'm stuck at a call center.
begging for votes.

393
00:27:41.745 --> 00:27:43.497
So that's really why you came here.

394
00:27:43.580 --> 00:27:46.124
He wants me to hack into
the voting machines. get him reelected.

395
00:27:46.208 --> 00:27:48.293
Nice try. K.G. Nice try.

396
00:27:50.879 --> 00:27:52.047
I need your help. Sam.

397
00:27:52.130 --> 00:27:55.008
Yeah. You wanted a general meeting
about cybersecurity.

398
00:27:55.592 --> 00:27:56.885
I need you to find someone.

399
00:28:01.181 --> 00:28:02.307
What kinda someone?

400
00:28:03.475 --> 00:28:05.227
A player in an online chess game.

401
00:28:05.310 --> 00:28:07.145
We have one player's username.

402
00:28:07.229 --> 00:28:09.439
so we just need to find out
who his opponent was.

403
00:28:09.523 --> 00:28:11.984
Doesn't exactly sound like
official government business.

404
00:28:12.067 --> 00:28:14.152
My sister Charlotte
flew in the Iran operation.

405
00:28:14.236 --> 00:28:16.029
Her sortie went very wrong.

406
00:28:16.113 --> 00:28:18.615
but she's the only one
of her squadron who survived.

407
00:28:18.699 --> 00:28:20.075
- Shit.
- Yeah.

408
00:28:20.659 --> 00:28:21.660
She okay?

409
00:28:21.743 --> 00:28:23.453
That's TBD right now. Her memory's shot.

410
00:28:23.537 --> 00:28:26.039
She had concerns about the mission.

411
00:28:26.915 --> 00:28:29.376
And then we managed to track down
a comms recording.

412
00:28:29.459 --> 00:28:31.879
- That's all encrypted.
- They weren't encrypted.

413
00:28:32.796 --> 00:28:34.423
We heard it. It's just 20 seconds.

414
00:28:34.506 --> 00:28:36.675
- but it was one of her concerns.
- Wait. wait. wait.

415
00:28:38.635 --> 00:28:41.555
What exactly did you hear. Dan?

416
00:28:46.435 --> 00:28:47.853
- What did you hear?
- Airplanes

417
00:28:47.936 --> 00:28:52.024
that were no longer controlled
by their pilots.

418
00:28:52.983 --> 00:28:56.486
Now our contact's gone missing.
along with the recording.

419
00:28:58.197 --> 00:28:59.907
You're not really his assistant. are you?

420
00:28:59.990 --> 00:29:02.409
Something really fucked up
happened on that mission. Sam.

421
00:29:02.910 --> 00:29:05.454
- And we have to find that recording.
- And you figured since we played

422
00:29:05.537 --> 00:29:08.498
"Don't You Want Me" and "Rich Girl". I'd
help you get access to military secrets?

423
00:29:10.626 --> 00:29:11.877
I have a sister too. Dan.

424
00:29:12.836 --> 00:29:15.172
And a wife. and kids.

425
00:29:16.798 --> 00:29:18.258
And I pledged my allegiance.

426
00:29:18.342 --> 00:29:20.802
And signed so many secrecy documents
you wouldn't believe.

427
00:29:20.886 --> 00:29:22.221
Except. no. you would believe

428
00:29:22.304 --> 00:29:23.931
- because you signed them too.
- Yeah.

429
00:29:24.014 --> 00:29:26.558
I have to take a lie detector test

430
00:29:26.642 --> 00:29:27.935
- every six months.
- Sam. Sam.

431
00:29:28.018 --> 00:29:29.394
- I get it.
- Do you get it?

432
00:29:40.531 --> 00:29:44.076
Listen. if it was my sister.
I'd want to know what happened too.

433
00:29:45.327 --> 00:29:48.872
Of course she's an insurance agent.
so unlikely.

434
00:29:53.293 --> 00:29:56.672
If you ever want to jam
for old time's sake.

435
00:29:57.881 --> 00:29:59.049
- call me.
- Yeah.

436
00:29:59.633 --> 00:30:01.927
Right. I better go.

437
00:30:10.394 --> 00:30:12.396
Okay. Now what?

438
00:30:18.986 --> 00:30:19.987
What?

439
00:30:21.071 --> 00:30:23.240
Yeah. that guy was at Alameda's funeral.

440
00:30:26.034 --> 00:30:27.995
He was at my office the day I was fired.

441
00:30:29.121 --> 00:30:30.122
You sure?

442
00:30:34.376 --> 00:30:36.253
Hello. Daniel. Helen.

443
00:30:36.962 --> 00:30:38.505
Why don't we grab a coffee?

444
00:30:39.715 --> 00:30:40.716
My treat.

445
00:30:45.345 --> 00:30:47.556
You're sure I can't get you anything?

446
00:30:48.682 --> 00:30:49.975
Helen. anything?

447
00:30:50.058 --> 00:30:51.268
- I'm good. thank you.
- Okay.

448
00:30:51.351 --> 00:30:54.146
I think we're all... we're all set.
Appreciate it.

449
00:30:56.106 --> 00:30:58.150
- Then I suppose I'll get to the point.
- What happened

450
00:30:58.233 --> 00:31:00.194
to our contact in Baltimore?

451
00:31:00.277 --> 00:31:03.155
Is he dead. or is he just
off being tortured somewhere?

452
00:31:05.574 --> 00:31:08.827
Steven Price now occupies
a highly coveted position

453
00:31:08.911 --> 00:31:12.039
at the Radford Group.
a cybersecurity think tank.

454
00:31:14.166 --> 00:31:18.337
I imagine you were thinking
of Senior Pilot Alameda's father.

455
00:31:18.420 --> 00:31:19.671
After his son's funeral.

456
00:31:20.297 --> 00:31:23.884
he received a very generous loan
to bail out his brother's woodworking shop

457
00:31:23.967 --> 00:31:26.094
- in Tehachapi. California.
- In exchange for what?

458
00:31:26.178 --> 00:31:27.387
If I may.

459
00:31:28.096 --> 00:31:32.643
the two of you are endangering
something very important.

460
00:31:34.853 --> 00:31:36.313
You didn't tell us your name.

461
00:31:37.648 --> 00:31:38.649
I usually like to know

462
00:31:38.732 --> 00:31:41.401
- who's fucking me over. even if they do--
- I am merely a representative

463
00:31:41.485 --> 00:31:45.489
of people who have the ability
to offer you a second chance.

464
00:31:47.074 --> 00:31:51.578
I imagine the <i>Times</i> was
a dream job at one point. yes?

465
00:31:56.416 --> 00:31:58.919
I've taken the liberty
of contacting the editor.

466
00:31:59.002 --> 00:32:00.838
He's open to meeting with you.

467
00:32:00.921 --> 00:32:03.924
despite your reputation
for journalistic fraud.

468
00:32:04.675 --> 00:32:10.222
It would be a shame for your talent
to go to waste over one mistake.

469
00:32:17.062 --> 00:32:19.523
Go fuck yourself. You got me fired.

470
00:32:19.606 --> 00:32:22.067
All it takes is one phone call.

471
00:32:22.150 --> 00:32:23.151
Think about it.

472
00:32:25.070 --> 00:32:29.575
Cool. So. what kind of cash and prizes
are you gonna offer me?

473
00:32:30.993 --> 00:32:33.245
In your case. Congressman.
it's not about you.

474
00:32:35.497 --> 00:32:38.917
How fucking dare he threaten
to withdraw care for Charlotte.

475
00:32:40.878 --> 00:32:42.129
Yeah. it sucks.

476
00:32:43.046 --> 00:32:44.756
- What?
- Sorry?

477
00:32:45.465 --> 00:32:48.302
That sounded like there was gonna
be a but there. It sucks. but...

478
00:32:49.636 --> 00:32:52.347
I mean. he wasn't technically threatening
to withdraw care for Charlotte.

479
00:32:52.431 --> 00:32:54.057
He just. you know.

480
00:32:54.141 --> 00:32:57.978
he said that the level of trauma therapy
the clinic provides is expensive

481
00:32:58.061 --> 00:33:00.397
- and outside of insurance. and...
- Sorry. I'm...

482
00:33:00.480 --> 00:33:02.774
I'm having a hard time
seeing the difference.

483
00:33:07.404 --> 00:33:10.282
I can... I'm a United States Congressman.

484
00:33:10.365 --> 00:33:11.491
I can get in front of cameras.

485
00:33:11.575 --> 00:33:12.576
I can tell 'em what we know.

486
00:33:12.659 --> 00:33:13.785
Which is what?

487
00:33:14.828 --> 00:33:17.122
- That Charlotte's mission was fucked up.
- Can you prove that?

488
00:33:17.206 --> 00:33:19.875
I can subpoena records.
I can subpoena the comms recording.

489
00:33:19.958 --> 00:33:21.835
Daniel. nothing will be found.

490
00:33:32.179 --> 00:33:33.305
Wow.

491
00:33:36.600 --> 00:33:38.018
You want the <i>Times</i> gig.

492
00:33:38.852 --> 00:33:39.853
Excuse me?

493
00:33:40.521 --> 00:33:42.231
Maybe it's time you open up
about your little.

494
00:33:43.357 --> 00:33:45.108
problem with journalistic fraud?

495
00:33:47.361 --> 00:33:49.571
If you had gone
beyond my LinkedIn profile.

496
00:33:49.655 --> 00:33:51.073
you would already know this.

497
00:33:51.698 --> 00:33:54.868
And of course I want a job at the <i>Times</i>.
you sanctimonious fuck.

498
00:33:55.619 --> 00:33:57.955
But I also want Charlotte
to get the care that she needs. you know.

499
00:33:58.038 --> 00:34:00.123
She's your sister. but she's my source. I...

500
00:34:01.416 --> 00:34:03.877
So what am I supposed to do?
Just supposed to go back to my cubicle?

501
00:34:03.961 --> 00:34:05.921
- I don't know. I don't know.
- Be a good dog?

502
00:34:14.221 --> 00:34:18.641
I just hope whatever you do.
will you please keep your head down?

503
00:34:18.725 --> 00:34:20.476
- There will be eyes on us making sure...
- Jesus.

504
00:34:20.561 --> 00:34:22.271
...that we got the message. Daniel.

505
00:34:28.819 --> 00:34:29.945
What are you gonna do?

506
00:34:33.447 --> 00:34:36.159
The ex is gone another week.
I'll hole up at his.

507
00:34:39.288 --> 00:34:40.664
I have to think. Daniel.

508
00:34:41.581 --> 00:34:42.583
You?

509
00:34:45.585 --> 00:34:47.420
Take me a week to catch up
on all the work I missed.

510
00:34:47.504 --> 00:34:50.424
so I guess I'll just go and do that.

511
00:35:00.934 --> 00:35:01.935
Congressman.

512
00:35:23.707 --> 00:35:25.042
What?

513
00:35:29.630 --> 00:35:30.714
I just...

514
00:35:36.011 --> 00:35:37.137
you know...

515
00:35:39.848 --> 00:35:44.269
they had me on all this...
the pills. the medicine

516
00:35:44.353 --> 00:35:46.522
and it fucked with my brain.

517
00:35:46.605 --> 00:35:49.024
but I get this feeling with people.

518
00:35:49.107 --> 00:35:50.609
Like with Knox.

519
00:35:51.610 --> 00:35:54.780
I don't know why. but every time
I fucking see him. I just...

520
00:35:56.448 --> 00:35:58.158
You two didn't always get along.

521
00:35:59.034 --> 00:36:01.245
I think what I'm trying to say is.
with you. I feel like...

522
00:36:01.328 --> 00:36:03.872
If someone would do anything to you. I...

523
00:36:06.375 --> 00:36:09.545
I don't know. it's. like. I would
kill them or something. you know?

524
00:36:09.628 --> 00:36:10.921
That's just what I meant.

525
00:36:14.341 --> 00:36:15.592
It doesn't matter. Just...

526
00:36:38.866 --> 00:36:41.034
Ossie. Ossie.

527
00:36:43.829 --> 00:36:45.289
Morning. Shirley.

528
00:36:45.789 --> 00:36:48.041
- What are you doing down there?
- I need two to go down.

529
00:36:48.125 --> 00:36:50.961
- Chair team will be here soon.
- No. Can't wait.

530
00:36:51.461 --> 00:36:53.922
We're not heavy. I trust your arms.

531
00:36:58.927 --> 00:36:59.928
Madam Mayor.

532
00:37:00.762 --> 00:37:01.763
Yeah.

533
00:37:07.519 --> 00:37:09.062
The main thing is.

534
00:37:09.146 --> 00:37:12.900
if anyone comes down in the next
half hour. even if they're raiders.

535
00:37:12.983 --> 00:37:15.986
could you just tell them
there's an equipment problem?

536
00:37:16.570 --> 00:37:17.863
That they have to wait?

537
00:37:21.575 --> 00:37:24.828
Yeah. We've been having issues
with the pulleys jamming.

538
00:37:24.912 --> 00:37:26.830
- Might take a while to get them free.
- Okay. Let's go.

539
00:37:26.914 --> 00:37:27.998
Great.

540
00:37:40.886 --> 00:37:43.055
Where the fuck have you been?
You've been gone all night.

541
00:37:43.722 --> 00:37:45.182
I was following Nichols.

542
00:37:45.265 --> 00:37:47.893
She and another woman
just went down the gap.

543
00:37:47.976 --> 00:37:50.729
- Who was the other woman?
- I think it was her friend. Shirley?

544
00:37:50.812 --> 00:37:52.648
- Oh. fuck.
- What?

545
00:37:53.649 --> 00:37:55.859
- What?
- What's with the face?

546
00:37:55.943 --> 00:37:58.320
Nothing. I just know...
I know where Juliette's going.

547
00:37:58.403 --> 00:37:59.988
- Mechanical?
- No. it's deeper than that.

548
00:38:00.072 --> 00:38:01.740
- I gotta--
- That doesn't change shit for us.

549
00:38:01.823 --> 00:38:05.118
Actually. it changes
everything for everyone.

550
00:38:05.786 --> 00:38:07.663
- Look. I need to go stop her. Get--
- Yeah. no.

551
00:38:07.746 --> 00:38:09.122
This again?

552
00:38:09.206 --> 00:38:12.334
Okay. You really
wanna know the truth so bad?

553
00:38:12.835 --> 00:38:15.295
- Let's go ask Juliette.
- She doesn't know shit.

554
00:38:15.379 --> 00:38:17.965
They got her on the forgetting drugs.
She didn't even know who we were.

555
00:38:18.465 --> 00:38:19.591
Well. maybe she would now.

556
00:38:19.675 --> 00:38:22.052
She knew who I was
when she saw me in the mines.

557
00:38:27.599 --> 00:38:28.600
Okay.

558
00:38:29.101 --> 00:38:30.352
Okay?

559
00:38:30.936 --> 00:38:32.187
How are we getting there?

560
00:38:33.021 --> 00:38:35.983
Well. he's got a way.
but you're not gonna like it.

561
00:38:36.692 --> 00:38:38.360
Don't listen to the kid.
You're gonna love it.

562
00:38:44.199 --> 00:38:46.034
Hey. hey. Get this shit out of here.

563
00:38:51.206 --> 00:38:53.333
What are you doing in my office?

564
00:38:56.712 --> 00:38:58.755
Sorry. I didn't see your badge.

565
00:38:58.839 --> 00:38:59.840
This your office?

566
00:39:00.674 --> 00:39:02.217
- Since...
- Since the current shadow

567
00:39:02.301 --> 00:39:03.927
hasn't shown for two days.

568
00:39:04.511 --> 00:39:05.971
McLain's nowhere to be found.

569
00:39:07.139 --> 00:39:08.557
Someone's gotta run this place.

570
00:39:09.474 --> 00:39:11.018
And you're that person?

571
00:39:12.811 --> 00:39:14.563
I'm McLain's former shadow.

572
00:39:14.646 --> 00:39:17.482
which makes me
more qualified than anyone else.

573
00:39:18.066 --> 00:39:21.904
And unlike the current shadow.
I've never missed a day of work.

574
00:39:22.863 --> 00:39:24.656
You're not too fond of Orla Kent?

575
00:39:25.157 --> 00:39:26.366
No. She took my job.

576
00:39:26.450 --> 00:39:28.076
Your name is Glenda?

577
00:39:28.160 --> 00:39:29.161
It is.

578
00:39:29.244 --> 00:39:30.621
So she took your boyfriend too?

579
00:39:34.833 --> 00:39:39.463
Listen. Mike Davidson is no more Orla's
boyfriend than you are mine. Sheriff.

580
00:39:39.546 --> 00:39:41.673
but he does like
to think everyone loves him.

581
00:39:41.757 --> 00:39:46.011
And sometimes because he's an asshole.
he'll go out of his way to prove it.

582
00:39:47.596 --> 00:39:51.141
So. she didn't take Mike from you.
but she did take your job?

583
00:39:53.143 --> 00:39:54.561
I shouldn't be so small about it.

584
00:39:55.062 --> 00:39:57.606
To be honest. losing the shadow job. I...

585
00:39:59.608 --> 00:40:00.817
I was a little relieved.

586
00:40:04.696 --> 00:40:05.739
Because?

587
00:40:06.323 --> 00:40:07.574
Because

588
00:40:08.659 --> 00:40:11.036
maybe it gave me
a chance to go home for a bit.

589
00:40:12.663 --> 00:40:15.165
That's on 70. The mines.

590
00:40:15.958 --> 00:40:17.334
Ed Harwood is your--

591
00:40:17.417 --> 00:40:18.418
Father.

592
00:40:19.795 --> 00:40:21.630
The legend himself.

593
00:40:24.883 --> 00:40:26.677
Somebody in trouble for something?

594
00:40:30.055 --> 00:40:32.140
When was the last time you saw Orla Kent?

595
00:40:39.022 --> 00:40:40.315
Wait.

596
00:40:42.192 --> 00:40:43.485
I know this place.

597
00:40:43.569 --> 00:40:45.112
You used to come down here a lot.

598
00:40:45.612 --> 00:40:46.989
You had a boyfriend.

599
00:40:55.163 --> 00:40:56.206
George...

600
00:40:58.208 --> 00:40:59.793
- Right?
- Yeah.

601
00:41:01.670 --> 00:41:03.422
You used to come down to the Void.

602
00:41:04.298 --> 00:41:06.383
You never told me about him. but I knew.

603
00:41:11.096 --> 00:41:13.765
I told you. Sorry.

604
00:41:15.350 --> 00:41:16.518
What are you doing?

605
00:41:18.395 --> 00:41:20.022
- What. Jules?
- Wait.

606
00:41:26.862 --> 00:41:28.780
Hey. hey. Can you hit the lights?

607
00:41:33.702 --> 00:41:34.703
Come and look at this.

608
00:41:36.371 --> 00:41:38.332
- Here.
- What?

609
00:41:39.166 --> 00:41:40.167
Here.

610
00:41:41.210 --> 00:41:42.211
Yeah?

611
00:41:45.756 --> 00:41:48.717
So there's gotta be a latch or...

612
00:41:50.135 --> 00:41:51.345
Some way to open it.

613
00:41:51.428 --> 00:41:52.679
What is this? Wait.

614
00:41:59.561 --> 00:42:00.854
Wait.

615
00:42:01.980 --> 00:42:03.190
Hey. hey.

616
00:42:09.238 --> 00:42:10.822
Walker said she sealed it off.

617
00:42:10.906 --> 00:42:12.032
Clearly not.

618
00:42:13.367 --> 00:42:14.743
I'll go see who it is.

619
00:42:14.826 --> 00:42:15.827
Take this.

620
00:42:16.328 --> 00:42:17.454
And shut the door!

621
00:43:52.841 --> 00:43:53.926
Hello?

622
00:43:55.010 --> 00:43:56.220
<i>Who is this?</i>

623
00:43:56.887 --> 00:44:00.182
Hi. this is Congressman Daniel Keene.

624
00:44:00.265 --> 00:44:01.433
Who do I have

625
00:44:01.517 --> 00:44:03.769
- the pleasure of speaking with?
- <i>K.G. K.G.. it's me.</i>

626
00:44:09.399 --> 00:44:10.400
Sam?

627
00:44:11.985 --> 00:44:13.946
- How did you--
- <i>I routed this through a burner.</i>

628
00:44:14.029 --> 00:44:15.072
<i>so no one can track it.</i>

629
00:44:15.155 --> 00:44:17.824
But I gotta be quick. so just listen.

630
00:44:17.908 --> 00:44:21.286
<i>What you said about
your sister's mission didn't sit right.</i>

631
00:44:21.912 --> 00:44:23.664
<i>All week I've had an itch about it.</i>

632
00:44:24.289 --> 00:44:25.749
<i>so I started scratching.</i>

633
00:44:26.834 --> 00:44:28.961
And that led me down
a full-blown rabbit hole.

634
00:44:29.461 --> 00:44:31.588
<i>I found something
you're not gonna believe.</i>

635
00:44:52.943 --> 00:44:54.278
Helen. you there?

636
00:44:58.699 --> 00:45:00.158
Daniel. what are you doing here?

637
00:45:00.242 --> 00:45:02.536
- Sam called. He did some digging.
- I thought he...

638
00:45:02.619 --> 00:45:05.455
- I thought he didn't wanna help out.
- He found something.

639
00:45:08.000 --> 00:45:10.752
Look. I know you said
you wanted to stop. but...

640
00:45:13.422 --> 00:45:18.427
Yeah. I don't know how
to do this on my own.

641
00:45:22.806 --> 00:45:24.850
- This is us.
- Since when do you drive a minivan?

642
00:45:24.933 --> 00:45:27.644
It's a rental.
From a guy who advertises on lamp posts.

643
00:45:28.228 --> 00:45:30.314
It's the closest thing I could get
to inconspicuous.

644
00:45:30.397 --> 00:45:32.024
- He took cash.
- Thank you.

645
00:45:32.107 --> 00:45:33.567
It could be stolen for all I know.

646
00:46:26.578 --> 00:46:27.579
Hello?

647
00:46:39.216 --> 00:46:41.009
Hello. Juliette.
